		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'd just use modulus (as the hardware would) except GBS files can have a non-power-of-two number of banks.</div>
<br />You can probably just pad the file with $FF (excuse me, 0FFh in Intel syntax because the Game Boy processor is a customized LH-0080, a Sharp clone of a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zilog_Z80" class="postlink">Zilog clone</a> of an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intel_8080" class="postlink">Intel design</a>) to the next power of two bytes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


